dct_title_s: PLANISPHÆRIVM BRAHEVM, Sive Structura MVNDI TOTIVS, EX HYPOTHESI TYCHONIS BRAHEI IN PLANO DELINEATA. [Amstelodami : Apud Joannem Janssonium, 1660]
dct_description_sm: Tycho Brahe’s theory of the universe is diagrammed.
Koeman IV, Cel 1(6); Celestial charts, antique maps of the heavens, p. 58-59 / Carole Stott. -- London : Studio Editions Ltd., 1995.
California is shown as a rounded island on small sphere (1.8 cm. diam.) showing north polar projection of earth (center of chart).

Issued in: Atlas coelestis; seu harmonia macrocosmica (Celestial atlas of universal harmony). -- Amsterdam : Apud Joannem Janssonium, 1660. Chart probably issued in 1708 edition published by Valk and Schenk.
